# Clean Architecture — Backend

## Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Owns | Must NOT Own |
|-------|------|--------------|
| **Domain** | Business invariants, entities, VOs, domain events | I/O, HTTP, DB, ML, config |
| **Application** | Use cases, port interfaces, DTOs | Framework code, concrete adapters |
| **Infrastructure** | Port implementations (repos, ML, external APIs) | HTTP routing, request parsing |
| **Interfaces** | HTTP handlers, schemas, DI wiring | Business rules, SQL, domain logic |

## Ports & Adapters

- Define **inbound ports** in `application/ports/inbound/`; implement in `interfaces/`.
- Define **outbound ports** in `application/ports/outbound/`; implement in `infrastructure/`.
- Use cases depend on outbound **abstractions**, never concrete adapters.

## Use Case Pattern

One use case class per user intent (e.g. `RecognizePlateUseCase`, `VerifyPlateUseCase`).

```
Handler → UseCase.execute(dto) → Domain + Outbound Ports
```

## Anti-Patterns (reject in review)

- God-service combining scan + verify + risk + report.
- Domain entity importing SQLAlchemy decorators.
- Handler calling `infrastructure/database` directly.
- Circular imports between bounded contexts — orchestrate in `application/use_cases/orchestration/`.

## Bounded Contexts

`officer` · `vehicle` · `vehicle_scan` · `plate_verification` · `risk` · `reporting` · `history` · `alerting` · `common`

Cross-context logic: application orchestration or domain events — not direct entity imports across contexts.
